4. Hex-Rays "Map to another variable"
If the decompiler is confusing two variables or you want to see if one value "flows" into another:
Shortcut: Use the = key (or right-click -> Map to another variable) in the pseudocode.
Use Case: This helps you unify local variables that IDA might have split, making it clear that a value from a function is being passed directly into another variable. 
